	Heaven	I have been to the One &amp; Only royal Mirage now 7 times and i can honestly say it is the best place for a holiday. On our last trip we had a new refurbed room on the ground floor over looking the pool it was out of this world. You have your own private beach with stunning views. The Staff are great and over the years we have got to know some of them very well. if you are looking for a great summers drink Roshin from the pool bar is your man. Also Stephen who is now the manager in olives is doing a revamp to bring everyone back to life and put the sparkle back into it. I have also Stayed in the JBH and i can honestly say i would never go back. They staff do not listen and they cant even get your drinks order right. It is filled with big brash tourist and not somewhere you can relax.	
	Predictably lovely	As part of One&amp;Only's Dubai presence, we found this hotel predictably lovely. It didn't exceed my expectations in any way however and if we return to Dubai (this was our first visit) I will try another of the top rated hotels.We stayed in a Gold Club room and, as others have outlined, the afternoon tea and evening cocktails were superb. We enjoyed breakfast at Celebrities more than at Olives. We thought the pool and surrounding area was beautiful and never had difficulty getting a good spot there - generally we went to the pool after a leisurely breakfast, after 11am. Sunloungers and shade are plentiful poolside. However, had we wanted a spot on the beach we would have been constantly frustrated as these were clearly reserved early. In general the staff were very good.I can't really criticise this hotel and we had a lovely stay. For a similar price, we have experienced significantly more luxurious rooms, better poolside service, better food and been made to feel more special and valued guests elsewhere - hence my expectations are very high and hard to exceed. I wasn't disappointed here and this review should be viewed positively.	
