	Fantastic hotel and service with only one caveat	Four of us recently stayed at The Palace for a week. Food as good as the Jebel Ali but rooms and service are much better. We stayed in Gold Club and service there from Maximillian (in charge), Raghu, Narayan and team was exemplary - nothing was too much trouble. &quot;Silver service&quot; afternoon team and evening cocktails were particular highlights, both socially and gastronomically. Pool service was very good and there were more than enough loungers, nice positions, towels, iced water refills etc etc. We heard no noise from The Palm construction etc - maybe the recession has halted it all! Half board gets you a great breakfast and OK dinner buffet (choice of 2 restaurants) but best to go to one of the many specialty restaurants. Each seems to have a menu for the half board option or you get 135 dirham (c. 27 euro) towards a la carte. Tagine (Moroccan) and The Beach (high level beachy) were outstanding. Great Indian restaurant also. Food in Eauzone was good but, if outside, make sure you get a table under an electric light. Even with 6 candles my wife couldn't see her food! Only caveat for the whole resort is the price of alcohol, which is very high even for Dubai. Cheapest wines c. 40 euro and glass of beer 8 euro. If you are a non drinker or a well-heeled drinker this is a great venue. This was our best hotel destination in Dubai yet.	
