Apr 20 2009 	What a lovely hotel	Have just returned from a week's stay at Royal Mirage Palace and fell in love with the place. It's beautiful, clean, well positioned and the staff are attentive and polite. Won't repeat the details about rooms or service at the pool area, suffice it to say that our standard deluxe rooms were well decorated, clean and spacious. Toiletries by Gilchrist &amp; Soames, replenished regularly. We arrived at about 10 in the morning after a night flight, and our rooms were not ready. (rooms ready at 2pm) However, after a very civilised check in we were able to have breakfast and then make use of the fitness suite showers and changing facilities to freshen up and get into our swimwear. Our rooms were not ready until 1.30pm, which was a slight inconvenience, but could not be helped because of our flight timings.Food quality at the hotel restaurants is excellent. Huge buffet breakfast/dinner at Olives. Beach Grill excellent, as was Tagine. Pool bar was very busy over the lunchtime period - they could definitely do with some extra tables there. Staff in abundance, but seemed unable to cope with demand at times. OH and son were able to watch football matches in the Rooftop Lounge at the Arabian Court, and the Arabian Adventures agent has an office in the hotel lobby for booking excursions.One thing not to be missed is the Oriental Hammam at the Spa (located by the Residence - middle hotel of complex) We decided to go for one of the numerous massage treatments on offer, and although men and women have their treatments at different times, you can still use the jacuzzi and sauna while your other half is having their treatment. Afterwards, some Moroccan mint tea in the relaxation room - I can honestly say it was a terrific experience, complete chill out in gorgeous surroundings.	
