Mar 16 2009 	What happened to this place?	This was my 3rd stay at The Palace, Royal Mirage. On the previous two occasions this was a near perfect resort, one of the best hotels I had stayed anywhere in the World. This visit was different. From reading some of the reviews it is possible visitors using the Royal Mirage for the first time may consider it an excellent venue. However, for a three time veteran this place has gone way down hill.... The service in many of the restaurants was terrible in comparison to previous years. There appears to be alot of new staff without the adequate training. The hotel has lost some of its best staff, probably to new hotels/restaurants. Service around the pool wasn't as attentive as usual, although the pool bar remains as good as ever. Seating for lunch is a problem and the menu limited (especially for those with children). We visited most of the hotel's restaurants during our stay. Service and food was not upto the usual quality you'd expect of the Royal Mirage e.g. drinks would be ordered, forgotten, re ordered, forgotten, then they'd appear on the bill... Overall there has been a general fall in previously very high standards. All in all very dispapointing this time around.. In the past I'd have happily recommended this hotel to anyone. I considered it one of the very best. Unfortunately, no more! Competition is fierce in Dubai and I'm afraid The Royal Mirage is in danger of losing it's top spot... Time to look elsewhere in my opinion, unless something is done to stop the rot...	
