Oct 23 2008 	Loved every second of our stay	We were a little apprehensive before we arrived after seeing the hotel ranking go from 3rd to 10th however from the moment we arrived we knew we had made the right choice and our concerns were soon at the back of our minds.The hotel staff were fabulous and went out of their way to make us feel welcome nothing was ever to much trouble. We were there to celebrate our wedding anniversary and the hotel arranged flowers and a champagne breakfast, they also presented us with a lovely leather picture frame.The room at the palace was clean and comfortable with a huge tv with the sports channels on for my husband and loads of closet space for me. We had a nice balcony over looking the swimming pool however we couldn't see very much as there were huge palm trees blocking the view. During our stay we had breakfast in both Celebrities and Olives, we would advise you to choose Olives out of the two as we had to wait 30 minutes to be seated in Celebrities. We also ate at Tagine, Beach bar and grill and Eauzone and had room service on 2 occasions. We can honestly say we didn't have one bad meal during our entire stay.We spent a couple of hours each day (thats all we could stand with the 40 degrees heat) on the beach which was immaculate, and the sea was like swimming in a huge hot bath tub and ok the view is not stunning as you can see the Palm being constructed however during the whole week we did not hear one noise coming from the Palm. So I really don't understand where people are coming from when they say there is constant noise it is absolute rubbish!The hotel staff working on the beach were fantastic keeping us topped up with iced water, cool towels, and fruit kebabs and also offering to clean our sunglasses. We chose not to sit round the pool as we prefer the beach however it did look very nice although it was very crowded. My husband also enjoyed a game of water basketball which was one of the activities the hotel arranges.For our anniversary I arranged the Seawings flight for my husband as a surprise, it was amazing and I would strongly recommend anyone to do it. It was great to see all the famous Dubai landmarks from above.We also did the Arabian Adventures trip called &quot;Just For You&quot; We were taken into the desert by 4x4 then met by camels which took us to our own private spot where we had our own waiter who cooked a delicious barbecue meal just for the two of us we were made to feel very special. It was a lovely romantic evening.We went to the Burj Al Arab for drinks in the Skybar which was also a fantastic experience you are given a one hour time slot when you book however we spent over 3 hours in the bar and nobody seemed to mind.We also got to wander around the Burj and take photographs without any fuss.I would also thoroughly recommend the Buddah Bar at the Grosvenor House Hotel. It was ranked the number 1 restaurant in the whole of Dubai and it was superb. Very very expensive I think we spent around £220 on a 3 course meal for two and we had a couple of bottles of wine but I would definitely go back again the food, the service and the atmosphere was top notch.Anyway back to the One and Only, the roof top bar at the Arabian Court was brilliant and a must for people to go to and have a drink at. Part of our holiday coincided with Ramadan and the hotel courtyards were transformed into Ramadan cafes which looked amazing.The only one negative point that I can say about this hotel is the lack of taxis. If you wanted to go out during the day time fine not a problem the hotel staff would call you a taxi however in the evening you had to wait until someone was being dropped off at the hotel so you could have their taxi, not as easy as it sounds if their are 5 or 6 couples all waiting at the same time, the bellboys issue you with a number and you have to wait until its your turn which is all well and good but sometimes it could take 10 minutes to wait for your turn other times it took up to 40 minutes. So if you have to be somewhere for a certain time in the evening it is best to plan ahead and give yourself plenty of time.I loved my time in Dubai and at this hotel so much that I am already planning my return trip! I would say the hotel has one of the best locations, right on the beach and within easy reach of all the major sights and shopping malls.It truly was a 5 star experience from the moment we arrived until the moment we left.	
