Sep 24 2008 	Hotel great but location not so great.	We've just returned from The Palace and have really mixed feelings about our holiday. Yes, the service at the hotel was fantastic, the staff really make your holiday special and were so sweet with our children. It's a shame the previous reviewer didn't rate Olives because the staff in there were so sweet to our children each night at dinner (though we chose to eat elsewhere once the babysitter arrived!), the food was decent but the decor a bit naff.The kids club was a bit of a joke, it was no bigger than our spare box bedroom at home with the TV on all day. They didn't allow children under 4 and yet everything in there was geared towards pre-schoolers. children are taken from each of the 3 hotels kids clubs to a bigger club which was great, it had a lovely outdoor paddling pool but once again, it was geared towards children aged 6 and under. Older children would probably be bored.As previous reviewers have mentioned, the pool is a really lovely space and the choice of restaurants fantastic. HOWEVER, the building works for the palm are right opposite the beach, so instead of having a beautiful view of the arabian gulf, you get to see tonnes and tonnes of cranes working all day, and you can hear them! I cant believe we are some of the only people on this site that have mentioned it. It felt like swimming in an estuary as opposed to the sea. So yes, the hotel is fantastic but really we could have been anywhere in the world and Dubai itself I guess just isn't my cup of tea, it's too fake and not finished. Next year I'll be making more of an effort to sit on a plane longer for a much better destination.	
