Aug 28 2008 	Slightly Disappointed	Having stayed at the Palace twice before, once in 2002 and once in 2004, we were really looking forward to our stay as this hotel had always been one of our real favorites.However, I now have to agree with one other reviewer who felt the hotel was getting complacent.On the plus side this is still a lovely hotel, with superb grounds and a lovely pool. The service is still good and very very good in the restaurants especially Nina's and Celebrities. However I had a very strong feeling that the level of friendlyness and service that you got by the pool was extremely dependent on how much was being tipped and did not like the fact that some guests were &quot;tipping&quot; the pool guys to reserve sunbeds - especially when they weren't bothering to turn up until midday!! This hotel used to have a policy where guests could not put towels on sunbeds unless they were actually going to stay by the pool. PLEASE return to this.I also felt that for a five star hotel the rooms, while absolutely spotless are getting a little tired. In our room the furniture was def in need of a upgrade. Also the lack of tea and coffee making facilities in the room needs to be put right.All in all we enjoyed our stay but felt that generally the staff were not as happy to be working at the hotel and serving the guests as they used to be. And this has, for us, changed the atmosphere. We were also lucky enough to stay at the Al Qasr at the Madinat in June and I'm afraid will be returning there in the future not the Royal Mirage, which is something I didn't think we'd say.Basically if this is your first visit to Dubai you will enjoy this hotel but if you are a returning guest I think you will notice a difference especially if you've tried other 5*+ hotels in Dubai in the meantime. Sorry Royal Mirage but I think you need to up your game if you are going to compete with some of the other hotels. Resting on a reputation isn't good enough.	
