May 14 2008 	Gem of a place!	We stayed here for 4 nights on the first part of our honeymoon. We were collected by a very helpful driver at the airport and taken to the hotel where 5 staff where waiting for us at the entrance. The 'gong' was sounded as we were taken through to the Gold room entrance for check in. Even though we arrived first thing our room was ready and the bags were brought up to us promtly. We had choosen a pool view but it was more a 'palm' view!The room itself was large with a very comfortable bed and luxury bathroom. As a 'gold' you had free breakfast up until 12pm, afternoon tea and cocktails in the evening which worked out really well. You also had free internet access 24/7 which was a bonus as some hotels still charge for the internet!The pool area was vast with plenty of seats even though it was busy. Sunglasses were often cleaned, fruit sticks and water were also often offered. The beach was private and clean but not as nice as further down towards the Burj. One day there was a boat race on and a helicopter that followed the circuit. The noise was horrendous and the helicopter flew over (extremely low) on several occasions to the point many people went inside. It was ashame as it ruined a peaceful afternoon. I am not sure if it was a one off or not.There are plenty of restaurants, The Beach was very nice.The staff in the Gold area where ever so polite and helpful. Nothing was a problem to them. They even charged my phone for me!Overall, a great stay at a hotel I have no problems in suggesting others to stay.	
