Aug 27 2007 	Service with an attitude	The hotel is split into 3 parts : the Palace (kind of glitzy, smaller rooms and small bathtubs), the Arabian Court (prettier and larger rooms, but bathtubs small) and the very snobby Residence (prettiest with big bathtubs). It's very pretty at night and the facilities are top notch.The biggest problem with the place is the attitude of some of the staff. Service getting drink in restaurants is HORRIBLY slow (I waited 35 mins and asked 4 times for a glass of water). There are more rules about where one can and can't go, with whom and how to act than in kindergarden. OK to smoke up common areas and say nasty things in French about other clients (as if we don't understand), but try to bring in a few friends for a drink to you room. Go to the Burj. They have a &quot;can do&quot; attitude and are much nicer to their clients.	
