Apr 10 2007 	Pure luxury	Have just returned from a weeks Easter break to the One and Only Royal Mirage in Dubai. The hotel and Dubai was absolutely fantastic! Can not wait to go back again. There is so much to do and so much to see that you cannot fit it into just one week. There is a lot of building work going on in Dubai at the moment, mainly in the marina area (top end of Jumeirah beach) and the central business area. This work does not impact on the Royal Mirage. You can see cranes etc in the distance, but no noise can be heard. The hotel itself if truly wonderful. We are a family of 4 with two adults and two children, and there was something for everyone. The ratio of staff to guests is very high, and their attention to detail is brilliant. Around the pool area and down by the beach there are staff who come round with continuous supplies of fresh iced mineral water and cold flannels. In the afternoon someone comes round with plates of complimentary fresh fruit and there is also a member of staff who comes round to clean your sunglasses! Every afternoon there are complimentary activities for children. This included free use of the pedalos and kayaks one day and free camel rides another. You can also have free snorkles and masks and body boards if required. The hotel also has the Givenchy Spa which is fantastic! Breakfast is served in the Olives restaurant. The food is typical buffet style that would be expected in any 5* hotel. We also ate at the poolside bar for lunch a couple of times and the food was really lovely and reasonably priced. Most evenings we took a taxi out to a mall or souk (taxis are really cheap and plentiful) and ate out. Food in restaurants was of good standard and very good value. All in all a fabulous destination and a luxurious hotel. Would highly recommend it.	
Apr 4 2007	Amazing	We stayed at the Palace at One and Only Royal Mirage for three nights in March 2007. We had booked a Double Deluxe room but unbelieveably got upgraded on arrival to an Executive Suite. The suite wasn't ready when we arrived so we went down to the Pool Bar to have lunch and our first impressions were really good and this was before we'd even seen our room/suite.The suite was huge with two furnished balconies one from the living area and one from the bedroom. There was a handwritten welcome note from the hotel manager along with a plate of handmade pastries which was a lovely touch. The furnishings were sumptuous and the living area was HUGE. The bedroom was fantastic and also very spacious. It was the nicest room I've ever stayed in. Throughout our stay we would arrive back to our room to find a note hoping we were enjoying ourselves, on our departure again there was a note asking if we needed help packing or with any aspect of our luggage and just before we left there was another letter and a box of chocolates.We ate at Eau Zone and Nina's restaurants both of which are at the Arabian Court part of the Royal Mirage, you get a shuttle bus over to it. Both restaurants were exceptionally good, the food in EauZone in particular was spectacular. For lunch we ate at the Pool Bar which was simple fare but really well done.All in all, the service at this hotel is perhaps the best I've ever come accross, the overall impression I got was that each and every member of staff genuinely wanted you to have the best holiday ever, they were constantly smiling and greeting you. The grounds, pool and beach area of the hotel were meticulously kept and again the staff at the pool and beach were great. We went sailing most days it was cheap and there was plenty of choice in terms of your options from Kayaks, to Hobie cats and Lasers right up to waterskiing from speedboats.The building work at the Palm Jumeirah development is quite prevalent while you are on the beach and indeed on the land side there is extensive building work going on in the area BUT hand on heart it DOES NOT adversely affect your enjoyment of the hotel or indeed your enjoyment of the entire Dubai experience in the least, in my view its exciting to be able to witness the development of such an amazing destination.I've been to a lot of hotels in Dubai through the course of my work but this beats all the others hands down. Its not the biggest hotel in Dubai but its DEFINITELY THE BEST!!	
