Dec 22 2006 	Gorgeous retreat	We have been to Dubai 3 times and stayed at the Palace Royal Mirage twice this year and on both occassions we had a wonderful time. The location, staff and hotel are all fabulous and we thoroughly ejoyed our stay.We ate at most of the hotel's restaurants - Tagine, Nina, Eau Zone, Olives (breakfast only), Dining room &amp; the Beach Bar and Grill. We also visited the Kasbar nightclub and rooftop bar which is beautiful.The food was always fabulous and the serivce attentive.We also ventured out of the hotel and ate at a number of other restaurants in various hotels &amp; complexes and it appears to be that restaurants across Dubai are exceptional.Dubai as everyone knows is a building site, but once inside your hotel you can not hear anything. The views are good from the hotel but you do see cranes which is of course to be expected.We treated ourselves to a Gold room on the second stay and I'mnot 100% convinced that the benefits are worth the extra cost. The room is the same as a deluxe room - the only difference to us seemed to be that you get your own check in area and food served throughout the day plus pre dinner drinks. - These were served however when you are getting ready to go out and the food throughout the day is more posh nibbles rather than 'lunch' food.On our second visit we were remembered by certain staff which is always nice to see especially as the hotel is quite large.I would also like to recommend a great jewellery shop at the Gold and Diamond Park - it's called Cara. The service is great and we bought a beautiful diamond solitaire at a good price. The ring was made to our requirements and two days later we went to collect it and watched the ring being set which was good to see. SInce our return to England we have had the ring valued at more than 3 times what we paid for it. I have absolutely no hesitation in recommending this hotel. Dubai is also worth visiting especially if you like shopping, sunbathing, eating great food and staying in luxurious hotels. I would also recommend that you venture into the desert to drive in the sand dunes.Go- you will love it!	
