Jul 8 2006	Once again - fabulous in every way	We have just returned from The Palace at the One and Only and once again absolutely adored this hotel. I visited last July and have always wanted to return and it was just as fantastic. This hotel is immaculate - I do believe that the high standards of this hotel make every guest feel as if they are the first guest to enter. From the moment we arrived till the moment we left we were looked after incredibly well. Breakfast each day was taken in Olives (the beds being so comfortable, for a girl who never manages to lie-in, I had to set the alarm in order to make last breakfast at 1030 hrs) and then the pool area for a few hours. With going in the heat of July, the hotel was not fully occupied (one of the huge advantages of going at this time), so it was always possible to get a well located sun lounger and parasol, or occasionally gazebo. In the afternoons we would pop out so we did Ski Dubai (great fun and not too expensive - around £20 for 2 hrs skiing), Emirates Mall and Madinat Souk.Our meals over our three nights were at Eau Zone, Beach Grill (our favourite) and Nina's. We booked our restaurants about a month in advance by email.At a drinks evening, we met several of the management and it was excellent to see how much they value the opinions of their guests.I can't wait to return - I would return in August if my husband would agree, but I think I'm going to have to wait until next summer. We had a glorious 3 night, 5 day break taking the late BA flight from Heathrow on Friday night and then the late flight out of Dubai at 11pm on the Tue. I believe we had service with a smile and service that cares - not always the same thing.	
