inatly loads cheaper - plus u can haggle!Water Park was under construction - it was ok ... nothing special but nice if u want somewhere different to go to break up the day!Cabs very cheap. Would definatlt definatly go there - the hotel is lovely and you get pampered! The hotel has 3 parts to it and you can use all 3 - there is a shuttle service to each one running up until aprox 12.30am but you can walk its just a lot easier. Enjoy!Alcohol expensive eg in the hotel 1 beer - £5 (english pounds)Basically definatly would reccommend - it was the most luxorious hotel Iv ever stayed in and Iv stayed in a few.	
Sep 24 2005	Go on - spoil yourself!	With its low rise Arabian inspired build, airy interiors, immaculate gardens and huge pool area with palm trees &quot;in&quot; the pool, you cannot fail to be impressed with this luxury resort hotel. No standing at reception to check in, you are taken to a sofa in the lounge and tea is brought for you while the receptionist deals with your details. From then on you quickly adjust to being pampered by the staff who are charming, friendly and respectful. We had a &quot;standard&quot; deluxe room overlooking the gardens/sea which was lovely with a stunning marble bathroom, separate loo, separate shower and a walk in dressing room. The &quot;room-boy&quot; was adorable and the bathroom cleaned and towels/robes replaced twice a day. The bed was turned down and a pair of curly Arabian slippers placed by the bed on a cotton mat. Room service was fast and my humble toasted cheese sandwich arrived on a huge tray with silver service and orchids. For me the pool area was pure heaven. Don't even think of carrying your own towels or bag to your cabana - iced water is brought regularly, as are cold guest towels, fruit kebabs and the famous sunglass cleaning service! (all complimentary). It is immaculately clean (the beach is cleaned every day too). The only people I would caution against staying here are those with a walking disability, because it is very &quot;spread out&quot; and spacious - although I am sure the hotel would arrange to have you carried everywhere!! Just a little note: Dubai is luxury hotels, shopping malls, ultra modern buildings, building sites, and desert. Not a lot else! Don't look for culture. The little museum is well worth a visit but it is more lifestyle than history. The whole country is staffed by (hardworking and polite) Indians who are shipped over, but that is another story. It is, however, extremely safe.	
